* Damage Adder missing pulses<br>
* Damage Adder stacking<br>
* Resist Chant Spam<br>
* Snare not getting aggro<br>
* Speed Song and Spindelhalla entrance<br>
<br>
Issues:<br>
* Realm Ability - Fury of the Gods needs review<br>
* Song of Rest needs a boost in power<br>
* Spell Sound Effects<br>
* Combining/Tweaking Resist Songs<br>
* Access to lower level Snare<br>
* Epic Armor Stats<br>
* Epic Armor look<br>
* Battlesong +items<br>
<br>
Requests: Defensive (If balance requires)<br>
* Evade II<br>
* HP boost<br>
* Medium Shields <br>
<br>
Requests: Songs (If balance requires)<br>
* Song of Haste<br>
* Song of Protection<br>
* Song of Evasion<br>
* Song of Endurance<br>
<br>
____________________________________________________<br>
<br>
Bugs:<br>
Realm Ability - Fury of the Gods:<br>
This skill is disppointing to say the least as our unique Realm Ability. It is the same concept as the Cleric's Bunker of Faith in reverse. Whereas the Cleric RA reduces group damage taken by 50% for 30 seconds, Fury of the Gods increases group damage for 30 seconds. Here is where the analogy falls short though. Fury of the Gods does not increase damage enough to warrant the purchase of this ability. It does not increase it to the same degree as a Cleric can reduce it. It also is rather costly for a skill (Compared to the Clerics 10 point RA). Consider dropping the cost of this skill to 10 points and increasing the damage in direct relation to the Cleric's ability to reduce it, or dropping the cost to 10 points and recycling it every 15 minutes. I do not like using a comparison like I have above, but it is the closest ability that matches. It does need to be tuned, otherwise it truly will be unique, as only a Skald who did not research the ability would purchase it. Also, keep in mind, since the damage adder dropping bug has not been fixed (still!), we lose our damage adder from this ability as well. Makes for a pretty useless RA.<br>
<br>
Damage Adder missing pulses:<br>
We lose our damage add about 1 time in 10 rounds. We believe this is due to the duration of the songs being set at 5 seconds and a pulse is 6 seconds. It leaves a window of 1 second that if you hit or lag in the least, you lose the damage add for that round. This also happens with the Song of Travel line of spells. Increasing our song duration to at lest the same length as a pulse (6 seconds) seems like it would fix the problem. 8 second duration would definitly cover the bug and also be to short to allow twisting (which is not a feature we want)<br>
<br>
Damage Adder Stacking:<br>
The sum of our damage add stacked with the one from a Runemaster or Shaman is equal or less than the solo value of our damage add. Why bother with stacking code if the result is inferior? <br>
<br>
Resist Chant Spam:<br>
We cannot toggle the spam generated by this song line with the options currently available in chat. It is extremely annoying to see the constant barrage of the song effecting and then wearing off.<br>
<br>
Snare not getting aggro:<br>
Casting at a distance will sometimes allow you to cast snare on a mob, and it uses power and endurance, but the mob does not get snared, nor do you get aggro from the mob. If you move closer and try to cast, the timer has been reset and you have to wait until the spell recycles. When this happens, you do not receive a resist message.<br>
<br>
Speed Song and Spindelhalla entrance:<br>
You cannot enter Spindelhalla when using the speed song. You get an out of bounds message. Turning it off or ‘W’alking is the only known way to access Spin<br>
____________________________________________________<br>
<br>
Issues:<br>
Song of Rest needs a boost in power:<br>
At higher levels, the rate of regeneration on this song makes it pointless to use except when soloing. In the 30's it is mildly useful, and at it's highest level it can be compared to putting a mini Band-Aid on a chest wound. Can we up the regen rate a bit?<br>
<br>
Spell Sound Effects:<br>
We love the spell effects, can we now get rid of the laser sound effects and give something more appropriate? It has been requested that the shouts actually sound like shouts, and that the songs sound like songs. Currently it sounds like those cheap ray guns you get at Wal-mart, that you are secretly happy about when they get broken.<br>
<br>
Combining/Tweaking Resist Songs:<br>
Review of resist songs and a request for the possibility to group them in some fashion to cut down on the number of spells. Maybe in sets of 2, cutting down the 6 spells to 3, or combining Songs and splitting between Skalds and another class.<br>
<br>
Access our lower level Snare shouts:<br>
Review of snare and it's power/endurance usage. It uses way to much at the higher levels for only an increase in time. Alternately, allow us to load up our older snare spell line so we can choose which of them we would use.<br>
<br>
Epic Armor Stats:<br>
Currently our Epic Armor is very heavy on Str and Con and light on Charisma. It would be nice if our armor would reflect our stats in their normal way, ie. Char/Str/Con, like our progresion does.<br>
<br>
Epic Armor look:<br>
There have been numerous mentions of dissatisfaction with the look of the Skald’s Epic Armor. If it would be at all possible, could we have a look that is not a copy of another realms’ armor? (But thank you for removing the Albion Grail.)<br>
<br>
Battlesong +items<br>
Through numerous tests by numerous Skalds we have finally agreed that +Battlesong items do nothing, or if it does do something, then the effect is unnoticable or effects something that we do not use. A review of the +Battlesong items needs to be made, and a decision whether the activate them as a functional item or change existing +Battlesong items to a stat that would benefit the Skalds.<br>
____________________________________________________<br>
<br>
Requests: Defensive (If balance requires)<br>
Evade II - Given at a high level, as the last class in the game to receive it. <br>
<br>
HP Boost - A review of our current HP and possible upscaling to give us longer life in battle.<br>
<br>
Medium Shields - Non-trainable, but available so we have more reason to use a 1-handed weapon and shield. <br>
<br>
Requests: Songs (If balance requires)<br>
These are just some song additions that have been thrown around to help with a variety of things from multi-skalds in a group to defense:<br>
<br>
Song of Haste - A chant spell to whip a group into a battle frenzy. Adds to attack speed. <br>
<br>
Song of Protection - A chant to increase armor class.<br>
<br>
Song of Evasion - A chant to increase evasion ability.<br>
<br>
Song of Endurance - At level 50, add endurance and/or power regen to the rest spell. Make it non-combat only. <br>
<br>
____________________________________________________________<br>
<br>
During the compilation of the report, an interesting topic came up. What exactly is a Skald? Is it a Light Tank, Support Class, or a combination of the two?<br>
According to the polling I did, the bulk of the Skalds believe themselves to be a combination of Suuport class and Light Tank. I agree with this assessment as the Skald is designed, and this report reflects the view of a Skald as a combination.<br>
If this is not the concept Mythic had in mind for the Skald class, then I have 2 other TL reports prepared to cover 'Skald as a Support Class' and 'Skald as a Light Tank'.<br>
